data.description: Built in 1990 this home has 3 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms and a 2 car detached garage. The front deck spans the entire front of the house with plenty of room for lounging or entertaining around the fire pit. Through the front door is the stairway to the second level.  To the right is the spacious living room with a high vaulted knotty pine ceiling, a ceiling fan, and a big bay window. The living room fireplace is river rock, woodburning, and imposing. The living room floor and stairs are carpeted. The front of the fireplace faces the living room while the side of it faces the dining room.  The dining room is light and bright with French doors leading to the outside deck. Adjacent to the dining room, the kitchen has tile floors and counter tops and stainless-steel appliances. A bay window sits over the kitchen sink for a great view. It has oak cabinets, recessed lighting, and a walk-in pantry. Conveniently, the stacked washer/dryer is located off the kitchen. To the left of the front door is the primary bedroom.  It has a vaulted ceiling, a bay window with a chaise lounge in front of it and a king-sized bed. The en suite bath has dual sinks and a walk-in shower. Upstairs, the second light and airy bedroom has twin beds, a wood art piece on the wall, a small seating area with a table, 2 chairs, and a lamp placed under the window. The third bedroom has one bed, a nice 2-tier office desk with lots of storage and a large flat screen TV on top. The property comes fully furnished.
